        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil half a kettle</p><p>Slice the<strong> red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and stir until dissolved</p><p>Once dissolved, add the <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>sliced red chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and set aside – this is your<strong> quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
