      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot over a medium heat with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained black beans</strong>, <strong>ground cumin </strong>and the <strong>remaining smoked paprika</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened – this is your<strong> black bean chilli</strong></p>",
